  • Method Details

    • getUserPassword

      public String getUserPassword(String hospitalID)
      Retrieves the password associated with a specific user by their hospital ID.

      This method reads the user data from the CSV file, searches for the user based on their hospital ID, and returns the corresponding password. If the user is not found or an error occurs, null is returned.

      Parameters:
      hospitalID - The unique hospital ID of the user whose password is to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      The password of the user, or null if the user is not found or an error occurs.

    • updatePassword

      public boolean updatePassword(String hospitalID, String newPassword)
      Updates the password of a user identified by their hospital ID.

      This method reads the user data from the CSV file, searches for the user based on their hospital ID, and updates their password. The changes are then written back to the file. If the user is not found, the password is not updated and false is returned.

      Parameters:
      hospitalID - The unique hospital ID of the user whose password is to be updated.
      newPassword - The new password to set for the user.
      Returns:
      true if the password was updated successfully, false if the user was not found.

    • isDefaultPassword

      public boolean isDefaultPassword(String password)
      Checks if the given password is the default password.

      This method compares the provided password to the default password ("password").

      Parameters:
      password - The password to check.
      Returns:
      true if the password is the default password, false otherwise.
